[div class=p 
	[em 
		"Lego Island 2: The Brickster's Revenge
	]em
	" is the sequel to the PC game 
	[em 
		"Lego Island
	]em
	" and had ports to other game consoles such as the PlayStation, Game Boy Color, and Game Boy Advance. The Game Boy Color version, compared to the other versions, is much simpler and lacks many of the minigames the other versions have. While there are action sequences, it is very dialogue driven and consists mostly of traveling from one place to another.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"The story is essentially the same as the other versions. Our protagonist Pepper has unwittingly let the Brickster escape from his prison by letting him eat enough hot peppers to breathe fire and melt down his prison cell. Pepper must now make up for this blunder and catch the Brickster so that he'll pay for his crimes.
	$LF
